// 2,160 student-facing handout tasks
// Keyed by HANDOUTS[level][theme][phaseId][activityIdx] → string
//
// Coverage: 6 levels (A1–C2) × 6 themes (identity, daily, work, travel, media,
// society) × 7 phases (with activity counts [8, 8, 8, 8, 12, 8, 8]) = 2,160 cells.
//
// Proficiency-exam alignment per level: A2 ↔ KET, B1 ↔ PET, B2 ↔ FCE,
// C1 ↔ CAE, C2 ↔ CPE. IELTS task types map across B1–C2 where relevant.
// SLA grounding follows the teacher-facing prompts in `examples.js`; the
// handout strings here are the *student-facing* instructions a teacher
// would print and hand out, framed in the student voice ("Your task", "You",
// concrete steps) rather than the teacher voice.
//
// Authored: A1 [x] · A2 [x] · B1 [x] · B2 [x] · C1 [x] · C2 [x]

